description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic FY3 doctor who is interested in gaining some academic experience, working at the interface of physical and mental healthcare. The NIHR MIC Oxford are undertaking a study of point of care testing for physical health disorders in community mental health settings across the SouthEast of England, funded by NHS England. We will evaluate the effect of these tests on the clinical pathway for people with serious mental illness, and whether they can help to improve health outcomes. The postholder will work alongside clinical academic psychiatrists and GPs,and will have the opportunity to develop skills in undertaking systematic review, quantitative and qualitative research methods, and in the dissemination of research. The post will provide an excellent starting point for someone considering a career in applied health research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Belinda Lennox;Professor of Psychiatry,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: belinda.lennox@psych.ox.ac.uk, Telephone number: 01865 218935&lt;/p&gt;
